<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="414" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="21.[169,1377,728,1274]" pageId="21" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,519,1122,1155]" pageId="21" pageNumber="414">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Mexican Long-tailed Shrew is found in Iztaccthuatl-Popocatépetl National Park and is threatened by deforestation outside the Park.
</paragraph>
